---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
import { getAffiliateCTA } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const tools = [
  { name: '10Web AI', slug: '/reviews/10web-ai', score: '8.8', price: '$10-60/mo', bestFor: 'WordPress users' },
  { name: 'Webflow', slug: '/reviews/webflow-ai', score: '8.5', price: '$18-212/mo', bestFor: 'Designers' },
  { name: 'Durable AI', slug: '/reviews/durable-ai', score: '8.5', price: '$15-100/mo', bestFor: 'Speed' }
];
---

<Layout title="10Web vs Webflow vs Durable: WordPress, Design, or Speed?">
  <StructuredData type="WebPage" data={{ name: '10Web vs Webflow vs Durable Comparison', description: 'Compare 10Web (WordPress), Webflow (Design), and Durable (Speed). Different tools for different needs.', url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/comparisons/10web-vs-webflow-vs-durable' }} />

  <section class="bg-[#FFF8F0] py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-5xl">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-2 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] mb-6">
        <span class="text-xs font-black">Jan 2025 · 3-WAY COMPARISON</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black">10Web vs Webflow vs Durable:<span class="block text-[#F5521A]">Different Tools, Different Goals</span></h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mt-6">WordPress power vs design freedom vs lightning speed.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">Quick Comparison</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {tools.map(t => (
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border-[3px] border-gray-200">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">{t.name}</h3>
            <div class="text-3xl font-black text-[#F5521A] mb-4">{t.score}</div>
            <div class="text-sm space-y-1">
              <div>Price: {t.price}</div>
              <div>Best For: {t.bestFor}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12 bg-[#F5521A]/10 rounded-xl p-6 border-[3px] border-[#F5521A]">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-4">Quick Verdict</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div><strong class="text-[#F5521A]">WordPress Users:</strong> 10Web AI (8.8) - Best if you want WordPress + AI</div>
        <div><strong class="text-[#F5521A]">Designers:</strong> Webflow (8.5) - Best for total design control</div>
        <div><strong class="text-[#F5521A]">Speed:</strong> Durable AI (8.5) - Best for 30-second websites</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">Feature Comparison</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full bg-white rounded-xl border-[3px] border-gray-200">
          <thead class="bg-gray-900 text-white">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">Feature</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold">10Web</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold">Webflow</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold">Durable</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Overall</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-[#F5521A]">8.8/10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">8.5/10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">8.5/10</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Design</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">8.5/10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-green-600">9.5/10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">6.5/10</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Speed</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">8.0/10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">7.0/10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-green-600">9.8/10</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">E-commerce</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-green-600">9.5/10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">8.0/10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">6.0/10</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Price</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-green-600">$10/mo</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">$18+/mo</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">$15/mo</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Learning Curve</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">Medium</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">Steep</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-green-600">Easy</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">When to Choose</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-blue-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-blue-700 mb-2">Choose 10Web If...</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-1"><li>✓ You love WordPress</li><li>✓ Need WooCommerce</li><li>✓ Want AI + WordPress power</li><li>✓ 70% affiliate commission exists</li></ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-purple-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-purple-700 mb-2">Choose Webflow If...</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-1"><li>✓ You're a designer</li><li>✓ Want total control</li><li>✓ Building complex animations</li><li>✓ 50% first-year commission</li></ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-orange-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-orange-700 mb-2">Choose Durable If...</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-1"><li>✓ You need a site NOW</li><li>✓ Want something simple</li><li>✓ Don't care about design</li><li>✓ Built-in CRM features</li></ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- My Experience -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-amber-300 p-6 md:p-8 rounded-xl">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">My Experience: Three Projects, Three Right Answers</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">Real testing, not theoretical comparison</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Last year I had three different website projects. Same timeline, different needs. Each tool was the perfect choice for one project—and the wrong choice for the others.</p>

          <div class="bg-amber-100 border-l-[4px] border-amber-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-amber-900 font-medium"><strong>Project 1: E-commerce store with 200 products</strong></p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Physical goods, variants, inventory, shipping zones, tax calculation. Needed serious e-commerce.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2"><strong>10Web:</strong> WooCommerce integration handled everything out of the box. Built store in 3 days. Client managing inventory easily. 6 months later: $47,000 in sales, zero technical issues.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Webflow:</strong> Would have required $212/month e-commerce plan. Less flexible than WooCommerce. Wrong choice.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Durable:</strong> No real e-commerce. Not even an option.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-orange-100 border-l-[4px] border-orange-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-orange-900 font-medium"><strong>Project 2: Design agency portfolio</strong></p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Visual showcase needed. Complex animations, micro-interactions, custom layouts. Design quality = revenue.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2"><strong>Webflow:</strong> Built completely custom portfolio in 2 weeks. Scroll animations, hover states, unique layouts per project. Clients were impressed. Landed 6 new projects first month = $42,000 in revenue.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>10Web:</strong> Would have been limited to WordPress themes. Not custom enough.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Durable:</strong> Generic designs. Would have hurt, not helped, a design agency's brand.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-yellow-100 border-l-[4px] border-yellow-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-yellow-900 font-medium"><strong>Project 3: Local plumber's service site</strong></p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Services, contact form, that's it. No one cares about design. Needed it fast, cheap, functional.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2"><strong>Durable:</strong> Generated complete site in 32 seconds. Spent 12 minutes adding phone number and service list. Published. Loaded in 0.9 seconds. Owner got 3 calls first week. Cost: $15/month.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>10Web:</strong> Would have taken 2+ hours. Overkill for simple service business.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Webflow:</strong> Would have taken 8+ hours. Completely wrong tool.</p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>The brutal truth:</strong> All three tools are excellent at their specific use case. None is "better" universally. The plumber doesn't need Webflow. The e-commerce store can't use Durable. The design agency would suffer with 10Web's limitations.</p>

          <div class="bg-red-100 border-l-[4px] border-red-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-red-900 font-medium"><strong>The mistake I see constantly:</strong> People pick the "best overall" tool for every project. They use Webflow for simple sites (wasting time and money). They use Durable for complex projects (hitting limitations immediately). They use 10Web when they don't need WordPress (paying for complexity they'll never use).</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-green-100 border-l-[4px] border-green-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-green-900 font-medium"><strong>The smart approach:</strong> Match the tool to the project. E-commerce? 10Web. Design portfolio? Webflow. Simple local business? Durable. This isn't about which tool scores highest—it's about which tool solves YOUR specific problem.</p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">I've built production sites on all three. Each one was the perfect choice for that specific project—and would have been the wrong choice for the others. Know what you're building BEFORE you pick your tool.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
